8.20	Elizabeth_Filkin	Elizabeth Filkin	Elizabeth Filkin (born 24 November 1940) is a British civil servant. She was the United Kingdom's Parliamentary Commissioner for Standards between February 1999 and 2002. On 18 July 2011, it was announced that Elizabeth Filkin would lead an inquiry related to the News International phone hacking scandal which would "recommend changes to links between the police and the media, including how to extend transparency."	
